Description. Adult male . Body 2.5 times as long as greatest width, dorsal surfaces smooth, widest at pereonite 4 , lateral margins weakly ovate. Rostrum present, anteriorly upturned and rounded. Eyes separated by about 33 % width of head, each eye made up of ~ 8 transverse rows of ommatidia, each row with ~ 6 ommatidia, eye colour black. Pereonites without transverse impressed line (absent on all pereonites);
pereonite 1 and coxae
2–3 each with posteroventral angle rounded; coxae 5–7 with incomplete oblique carina; posterior margins of pereonites 5–7 smooth, without nodules or setae.
